article.headline: S. Dakota St. 79, Idaho St. 47
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Clint Sargent scored 16 points to lead four South Dakota State players in double digits as part of a 79-47 win over Idaho State on Tuesday night. Griffan Callahan helped out with 13 points while Nate Wolters and Chad White each added 10. The Jackrabbits (4-0) shot about 48 percent from the field, including hitting 8 of 20 from 3-point range. They led 34-18 at halftime and never looked back. Deividas Busma led the Bengals (1-3) with 12 points and eight rebounds.
